metadata.name: O Fortuna #130
metadata.description:
"O Fortuna
Velut Luna
Statu variabilis

Semper crescis
Aut decrescis
Vita detestabilis
Nunc obdurat
Et tunc curat
Ludo mentis aciem
Egestatem
Potestatem
Dissolvit ut glaciem

Sors immanis
Et inanis
Rota tu volubilis"

As in the story of "Carmina Burana: O Fortuna", nothing is permanent, everything fluctuates, an emotional rollercoaster, sometimes up, sometimes down. The present situation should not define you, as your circumstances are ever-changing and uncertain. Remember that tomorrow is a new day and with it comes new opportunities for growth and improvement.

[S] to save a image file

made with p5.js , p5.js.noise
2023

metadata.name: Intuition #17
metadata.description:
I used to stare at the sky at night since I was a child.
In my imagination, I visited all the stars and flew from them to bigger planets... 

Maybe we are not the only beings in the galaxy.

Let's be kinder to everything


Be patient, it takes time for the full result

metadata.name: GRAVITATE #33
metadata.description:
Each piece in this collection is made from the simple concept of layering grids of circles. The varying grid sizes, circle sizes, positions and colors combine to create interesting dithering effects. There are seven color palettes in the algorithm and these range from low contrast, muted palettes (e.g. Mystic Sands) to high contrast, super saturated palettes (e.g. Inferno).

- - -

GRAVITATE is my first generative art collection and was made using only p5.js.

- - -

Commands:
Press `1` to save a low-res PNG 1200x1800
Press `2` to save a high-res PNG 4800x7200

Note that it may take up to 10secs for the image render to complete.

metadata.name: Oculus prime #3
metadata.description:
Is it an eye, a camera lens or something else entirely? We’ll never know.

Click the canvas to trigger a random shift in rotation, size and alignment. A random sound effect or chord will get triggered as well.

There are mainly 3 different sounds to obtain. A set of camera autofocus effects, and a harmonised pluck sound that comes in two different pitches and speeds.

There are a various amount of shapes and features that are randomised such as different sizes, colors, movements, thicknesses and so on.

The scene is covered in different configurations of Bloom and Noise effects. Unfortunately a lot of mobile devices are unable to handle it due to performance issues, hence I’ve been forced to disable the bloom effect on touch devices. I recommend playing with your minted specimen in a separate window on a computer in order to achieve the best look and smoothness.

@computeremotions - 2023-01-11

metadata.name: Terraced #17
metadata.description:
terraced craters
towering mountains
tranquil colors
dimetric

* this is an animated artwork, the animation loops, its duration depends on the piece, it can be paused by pressing 'p'
* this is a somewhat interactive artwork, click and drag to rotate around/above the object, scroll to zoom in/out
* the current view can be downloaded by pressing 'd'

I began exploring terraced reliefs 3 years ago, starting with lines and cellular noise, and eventually flat colors that turned into subtle gradients.
During that time, the visual concept oscillated between minimalism and busy images. I dropped the cellular noise, replacing it with 2D simplex noise modifying points on the dual grid.
The result is finally something that produces the iterations that keep me happy, something soothing and quiet. Spend some time with it, see how the light changes the landscape.

Best viewed in landscape mode, 3/2 or 16/9.

metadata.name: Ersbla #555
metadata.description:
Ersbla is part of the fxhash live minting experience at Proof of People, London 2022. 

It is the third entry in a series of abstract generative experiments inspired by the graphic and textile work of Anni and Josef Albers. As a follow-up to the 'Sabler' and 'Lebras' collections, 'Ersbla' produces textile effects using a combination of thousands of tiny dots arranged on variable grids, resulting in a wide variety of unique Bauhaus-inspired compositions in a variety of palettes.

Press 'S' to save a high-resolution 2400 x 3396 px image in PNG format.

Depending on the density of your output, please allow up to a few seconds for your edition to generate.

metadata.name: Moonlines #54
metadata.description:
The Moonlines project explores the combination of minimalist forms and basic rules to create complex images.

It uses a simplistic approach to combine 4 sets of parallel lines and a main shape in its center.

The overlapping and intersection of slightly slanted lines can generate beautiful interferences that result in complex moiré effects.

Artist: Estienne
March 2022
NFT 2.0 License

metadata.name: Florescence #116
metadata.description:
Digitally crafted flowers in pots for virtual window sills.

In the spirit of the piranha plant from the Mario Bros videogame. We wanted to create a project that acknowledges the playful depiction of nature in early videogames by creating a retro futuristic collectible that explores aesthetics over gameplay, whilst preserving the playful energy of these early digital worlds. There are many game elements that have emerged over the years that have become iconic in their own right. Their memorable designs have come to represent the exciting feeling of when we first discovered these worlds, but over time an appreciation for their simple design execution, harmony and balance has emerged. Art can exist in many forms and places including a digital pot plant.

Rarity:

There are a total of 23 hand-drawn and animated sprites divided into 4 groups Firelillies, Flytraps, Quasars and Stargazers and there are 15 possible combinations made from these 4 groups. 18% of the collection is a combination of these 4 groups which we can call random and the remaining 72% is divided between the remaining 14 combinations.


There are 3 possible grid systems 1x1, 3x3 and 4x4 

3% 1x1

40% 3x3

57% 4x4



There are 14 possible placement points for all grids and 76 stem/sprite arragement in total



For the pots and stems there are 11 colors to choose and  no rarities for color combinations.



The flower distribution can be either symmetric or random. 35% symmetric and 65% random



Export options:

Pressing 's' on desktop or holding for 2 seconds will download gif to whatever the current device resolution is. To export at a different resolution open the token in new window by clicking 'open' link under the token image and add "&exportsize=1080" or "&exportsize=2160" to end of the url and hit enter then either hold for 2 seconds or press 's' to create gif and download.
